        h2.fz-h2 Server Administration
        p Discounts apply to ordering new flexible configurations based on Xeon E5-2620v4, Xeon 2xE5-2620v4, AMD Ryzen 9 3900X and AMD Ryzen 9 5950X processors for the entire lease period of a dedicated server with a one-time payment for the specified period (1, 3, 6 or 12 months ).
        p Discounts: - 20% servers with Xeon E5 - 2620v4; -25 % for servers with Xeon 2xE5 - 2620v4; -50 % for servers with AMD Ryzen 9 5950X and 3900X.
        p The discount applies only to the servers listed in the terms of the promotion, ordered through the configurator on the main page of the site.
        p During the promotion period, the user can order any number of new servers (provided that the configurations listed in the promotion conditions are available).
        p Ready-made configurations do not participate in the promotion.
        p Discounts of 20, 25 and 50% apply to the following resources: processor, platform, RAM, disks (HDD/SSD/NVMe).
        p Discounts do not apply to additional services: OS, additional IP addresses, backup disk, backup, domains, control panels, licenses, technical support services, traffic, etc.
        p If you cancel the server for the promotion, the discount is not transferred to other services.
        p The offer is not valid simultaneously with other discounts and promotional codes for dedicated servers.
        h3.fz-h3 Filling in the details for invoicing
        p If you are issuing an invoice for the first time, after that the system will prompt you to fill in the data about the payer. They include the name of the company / full name of an individual, country of incorporation, type of organization (legal entity, individual or individual entrepreneur), address of the organization, TIN and KPP:
        h4.fz-h4 Filling in the details for invoicing
        p If you have already issued an invoice and filled in the payer's data in your Personal Account, the system will automatically prompt you to select it and issue an invoice using the previously filled in details. Before paying, do not forget to check that your details on the invoice are correct. If necessary, you can edit them in the Client â€” Payers section.
